{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χροιά</b>, <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> and <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>χροιή</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.164, 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1017 (in Callias Epigrammaticus “Lav. Pall.” 28 χροϊά (χροίην codices))\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <i>Attic dialect</i> <b>χροιά</b> and <b>χρόα</b>, the latter always in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus (see. below), also in 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “D.” 3.9, _sign._ 5, +others (see. χρώς)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>skin,</b> especially of the human body, hence <b>the body</b> itself, παραδραθέειν φιλότητι ᾑ χροιῇ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” [same place]; κατὰ χροιὴν ῥέει ἱδρώς 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus [same place]; ὄζειν.. τῆς χρόας ἔφασκεν ἡδύ μου 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1020 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ἐξανθεῦντα ἐς τὴν χροιὴν (<b>skin, surface</b>) ἢ χροιῇ (<b>colour,</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" signification 11) ἢ οἰδήμασι 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ τέχνης” 9: compare χρώς. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, 'skin', i.e. <b>surface,</b> Pythagorean term, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Sensu” 439a31, “Placita Philosophorum” 1.15.2, “Theologumena Arithmeticae” 18(_plural_); χ. ἐπίπεδος [prev. work]10; so perhaps in 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 81, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ σημείων καὶ σημειώσεων” 5, +others \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>appearance</b> to the eye, of heavenly bodies, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “D.” 3.9. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>superficial appearance</b> of a thing, its <b>colour,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 451, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 493, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 517 (Lyric poetry); παντοδάπαισι μεμειχμένα χροίαισιν 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica 20, compare 2nd c.AD: Numenius Apamensis Platonicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 7.282a \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; τοιοῦτον (i.e. ἐρυθρόν) εἶναι τῇ χροιᾷ τὸ μέλι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Antro Nympharum - Porphyrii Opuscula” 16; ἔστιν.. χρόα ἀπορροὴ σχημάτων ὄψει σύμμετρος καὶ αἰσθητός 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Meno” 76d; νόμῳ χροιή.. ἐτεῇ δ᾽ ἄτομα καὶ κενόν 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 125, compare 5th c.BC: Anaxagoras Philosophus 4, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Sensu” 440a8; ἐκ τριῶν τὰς χρόας ἅπασας μεμεγμένας, τοῦ φωτός, καὶ δι᾽ ὧν φαίνεται τὸ φῶς, καὶ τῶν ὑποκειμένων χρωμάτων [prev. author] “Col.” 793b33. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> especially <b>colour of the skin, complexion,</b> χροιῆς ἄνθος ἀμειβομένης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 27.6; χροιᾶς ἀμείψεις ἄνθος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 23; χροιὰν ἀλλάξασα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 1168; λευκὴν χ. ἐκ παρασκευῆς ἔχεις [prev. author] “Ba.” 457, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1012 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; χρόᾳ ἀδήλῳ τῶν δεδραμένων πέρι <b>with colour</b> that gives no hint of what has passed, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1318 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χρόαν.. τὴν σὴν ἥλιος.. αἰγυπτιώσει[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Pl.Com(?). p.615K. (post “fragment” 55); χρόας κάλλος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 196a; ἐρίζοι καὶ γάλακι χροιήν 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hecale” 1.4.3. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in Music, <b>nuance</b> of a scale, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.1143e.—On the accent, see Hdn.Gr.1.301, +others \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9759","accentedUnicode":"χροιά","shortDef":"complexion","mediumDef":"complexion","stepGloss":"complexion","stepTransliteration":"chroia","_step_Type":"word"}]}